- RMSE (Root Mean Square Error) is a measure of the difference between values predicted by a model and the actual values; 
- A higher RMSE indicates poorer performance;
- The threshold of 50,000 is considered critical for model performance in this context.

High Pearson's R values indicate strong positive linear correlation between predicted and actual values; 
Low RMSE values indicate high accuracy of the model; 
 Engineers are considered knowledgeable about model performance metrics.
